items.title: ‘Quality’ Stocks Just Ain’t What They Used to Be
items.description: FEATURE  “Quality” stocks are supposed to perform well in a volatile market. That hasn’t been the case this year.   This year’s market has certainly been volatile. Between President Donald Trump’s tariffs, the debate over the “One Big Beautiful Bill,” and the war between Israel and Iran, it has been a choppy ride for the which has managed a small gain this year despite a 19% drop earlier this year.
